Consider these two series:

$\begin{align}
\textrm{I}.&\displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\dfrac{(-1)^n}{n^{^p}}
\\\\
\textrm{II}.&\displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{n^{^p}}
\end{align}$

**Pick all of the following values of $p$ for which series $\textrm{I}$ converges and series $\textrm{II}$ diverges.**

[[☃ radio 1]]

